@startuml brain_maturation
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam titleFontSize 18

title Prefrontal Cortex Maturation\nWhy the Framework Extends to Age 35

map "Age 0–5: Foundation" as a1 {
  Brain => Rapid synaptogenesis, emotional wiring
  Male PFC => Forming
  Female PFC => Forming
  Style => Model, protect, expose
}

map "Age 6–12: Exploration" as a2 {
  Brain => Synaptic pruning, specialization
  Male PFC => Pruning
  Female PFC => Pruning
  Style => Encourage, track, don't direct
}

map "Age 13–17: Formation" as a3 {
  Brain => Limbic system dominates
  Male PFC => Immature
  Female PFC => Approaching maturity
  Style => Firm boundaries + increasing autonomy
}

map "Age 18–24: Launch" as a4 {
  Brain => PFC gaining ground
  Male PFC => Still developing
  Female PFC => MATURE (~21–24)
  Style => Advise, don't control
}

map "Age 25–30: Consolidation" as a5 {
  Brain => Full myelination completing
  Male PFC => MATURE (~25–30)
  Female PFC => Mature
  Style => Peer relationship
}

map "Age 31–35: Stewardship" as a6 {
  Brain => Pattern recognition, wisdom
  Male PFC => Fully operational
  Female PFC => Fully operational
  Style => Legacy transfer
}

a1 -down-> a2
a2 -down-> a3
a3 -down-> a4
a4 -down-> a5
a5 -down-> a6

note right of a4
  Female PFC matures ~21–24
  (Ingalhalikar et al., 2014)
end note

note right of a5
  Male PFC matures ~25–30
  (Giedd/NIH, Lebel & Beaulieu 2011)
end note

note bottom of a6
  Sources:
  • Giedd, J.N. — NIH Longitudinal Study
  • Lebel & Beaulieu (2011)
  • Ingalhalikar et al. (2014) U. Penn
  • Casey, B.J. et al. (2008)
end note

@enduml
